Johnny's loss in the UK isn't based on 'the truth', it makes NO difference who hit who, why, where or if any hits or orgasms were even involved. British law does not concern itself with that in slander/libel cases, rather, the plaintiff must prove that the slander was meant 'maliciously', designed to harm...
There is no burden of truth to the statements one way or the other, the sun tabloid simply has to say "it's just a story, we meant no judgement/harm either way..."
